<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17510523-7">
               <interp inst="t17510523-7" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510523-7" type="year" value="1751"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510523-7" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17510523"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17510523-7" type="date" value="17510523"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17510523-7-off39-c55" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510523-7-defend66 t17510523-7-off39 t17510523-7-verdict43"></join>
         
               <p>357. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17510523-7-defend66" type="defendantName">
                     Richard 
                     Beard 
                  <interp inst="t17510523-7-defend66" type="surname" value="Beard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-defend66" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-defend66" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17510523-7-off39" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-off39" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-off39" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one cloth jacket, one pair of canvass trowsers, one linen shirt, one canvass bag, the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17510523-7-victim68" type="victimName">
                           Henry 
                           Richardson 
                        <interp inst="t17510523-7-victim68" type="surname" value="Richardson"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17510523-7-victim68" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17510523-7-victim68" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                      
                  ; five shirts, three pair of stockings, one hat, one wig, one silk handkerchief, two pillowbears
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17510523-7-victim70" type="victimName">
                     David 
                     Farley 
                  <interp inst="t17510523-7-victim70" type="surname" value="Farley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-victim70" type="given" value="David"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-victim70" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17510523-7-cd40" type="crimeDate">April 28</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510523-7-off39 t17510523-7-cd40"></join> ++.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510523-7-person71">
                  Henry 
                  Richardson 
               <interp inst="t17510523-7-person71" type="surname" value="Richardson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-person71" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-person71" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t17510523-7-person72">
                  David 
                  Farley 
               <interp inst="t17510523-7-person72" type="surname" value="Farley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-person72" type="given" value="David"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-person72" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were two <rs id="t17510523-7-viclabel41" type="occupation">sailors</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510523-7-victim68 t17510523-7-viclabel41"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510523-7-victim70 t17510523-7-viclabel41"></join> belonging to the <placeName id="t17510523-7-crimeloc42">ship call'd the Friends Glory, a New-Castle collier, lying near Execution-dock</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17510523-7-crimeloc42" type="placeName" value="ship call'd the Friends Glory, a New-Castle collier, lying near Execution-dock"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17510523-7-crimeloc42" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510523-7-off39 t17510523-7-crimeloc42"></join>; they missed the things mentioned taken out of their chests; they were told the prisoner had been on board; he had formerly sailed on board the same ship; they went and found him, and be confess'd he had taken the things, and directed them to them in an empty house where they found them. Some of them were produced in court and deposed to.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17510523-7-verdict43" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-verdict43" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17510523-7-punish44" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510523-7-punish44" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510523-7-defend66 t17510523-7-punish44"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
